    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-03-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-03-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="108"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d108">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Italian Chargé</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-03-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 31, 1906</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 348.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note of the 23d instant, asking this department to use its good offices
                    with the executive department of the State of Ohio to obtain the withdrawal of
                    an order, issued by the food commissioner of that State, prohibiting the sale of
                    paste colored with saffron, the order, in your opinion, not being justified by
                    the provision of law on which it is based nor by the nature of the coloring
                    matter.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to say in reply that the department has at once communicated
                    with the governor of Ohio on the subject.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Bacon.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
